Copy tc++ (compiled execution file) to this directory and then type
    python3 test.py
to verify that your installation was successfully done.

[NOTE]
python2 is not supported.

[NOTE]
DO NOT use the input files (including pseudopot.) provided here for your research.
These were made only for test calculation...

[NOTE]
test_full1.py, test_full2.py, and test_full3.py are given for developers, which will take > 30 minutes in total.

[NOTE]
"reads_binary false" is specified in "input.in" provided here.
This option is used only for test calculation, where environment-dependent binary files are not appropriate.
You will not use this option in your research.
